1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,449
When is a person too young?

2
00:00:02,879 --> 00:00:07,969
The I'm-too-young variety of age excusitis does much damage, too.

3
00:00:08,239 --> 00:00:13,329
About a year ago, a twenty-three-year-old fellow named Jerry came to me with a problem.

4
00:00:13,520 --> 00:00:15,570
Jerry was a fine young man.

5
00:00:15,679 --> 00:00:19,650
He had been a paratrooper in the service and then had gone to college.

6
00:00:19,839 --> 00:00:27,090
While going to college, Jerry supported his wife and son by selling for a large transfer and storage company.

7
00:00:27,279 --> 00:00:31,489
He had done a terrific job, both in college and for his company.

8
00:00:31,919 --> 00:00:34,050
But today Jerry was worried.

9
00:00:34,399 --> 00:00:37,889
Dr. Schwartz, he said, I've got a problem.

10
00:00:38,079 --> 00:00:41,409
My company has offered me the job of sales manager.

11
00:00:41,599 --> 00:00:44,929
This would make me supervisor over eight salesmen.

12
00:00:45,520 --> 00:00:49,170
Congratulations, that's wonderful news, I said.

13
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:50,929
But you seem worried.

14
00:00:51,839 --> 00:01:01,250
Well, he continued, all eight men I'm to supervise are from seven to 21 years older than I. What do you think I should do?

15
00:01:01,359 --> 00:01:11,409
Can I handle it?" Jerry, I said, the general manager of your company obviously thinks you're old enough or he wouldn't have offered you this job.

16
00:01:11,679 --> 00:01:16,369
Just remember these three points and everything will work out just fine.

17
00:01:16,369 --> 00:01:19,570
But first, don't be age-conscious.

18
00:01:19,839 --> 00:01:24,770
Back on the farm, a boy became a man when he proved he could do the work of a man.

19
00:01:24,960 --> 00:01:29,489
His number of birthdays had nothing to do with it, and this applies to you.

20
00:01:29,759 --> 00:01:35,889
When you prove you are able to handle the job of sales manager, you're automatically old enough.

21
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:40,290
Second, don't take advantage of your new gold bars.

22
00:01:40,399 --> 00:01:42,210
Show respect for the salesmen.

23
00:01:42,399 --> 00:01:44,290
Ask them for their suggestions.

24
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:48,369
Make them feel they are working for a team captain, not a dictator.

25
00:01:48,639 --> 00:01:52,369
Do this and the men will work with you, not against you.

26
00:01:53,040 --> 00:01:56,929
Third, get used to having older persons working for you.

27
00:01:57,199 --> 00:02:02,849
Leaders in all fields soon find they are younger than many of the people they supervise.

28
00:02:03,119 --> 00:02:05,969
So get used to having older men work for you.

29
00:02:06,079 --> 00:02:11,090
It will help you a lot in the coming years, when even bigger opportunities develop.

30
00:02:11,359 --> 00:02:17,010
And remember, Jerry, your age won't be a handicap unless you make it one.

31
00:02:17,679 --> 00:02:19,730
Today, Jerry's doing fine.

32
00:02:19,759 --> 00:02:25,810
He loves the transportation business, and now he's planning to organize his own company in a few years.

33
00:02:26,719 --> 00:02:30,849
Youth is a liability only when the youth thinks it is.

